⏺ Done. Both files pass ruff and mypy clean.

  src/lf_client/rag_demo.py wires up the real TwoStageRetriever + ClaudeClient
  (api_key from env, Langfuse via get_client()) and runs the three queries,
  printing refusals vs. answers with sources and confidence — matching your
  template, plus a cost line and langfuse.flush() at the end so traces actually
  land.

  The day's success criterion (query 2 → refusal) is enforced in
  grounded_generator.py by the pre-generation confidence gate: if the top-1
  reranker score is below confidence_threshold (0.4), answer() returns
  is_refusal=True with refusal_reason="low_confidence (...)" without calling 
  Claude — so no tokens spent and no chance to hallucinate.

  To actually run it you'll need Qdrant up (localhost:6333) and
  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY set:

  .venv/bin/python -m lf_client.rag_demo

  One thing to verify empirically when you run it: whether the live reranker
  score for "parallel tool calls" actually falls below 0.4. If it refuses →
  threshold is well-tuned. If it answers anyway → bump confidence_threshold
  (e.g. GroundedGenerator(..., confidence_threshold=0.5)) until the unanswerable
  query gets rejected while the two answerable ones still pass.

